        {
            "id": "tradingview:c76f77a49f3d4:0",
            "title": "NVR reports Q2 net income $236.5M, EPS $83.96; revenues $2.33B",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-Xl9a4Ubk body-nzzZVyQ3 content-nzzZVyQ3\"><div class=\"symbolsContainer-uFduEtAF logosContainer-diQOvrPB\" data-no-swipe=\"true\"></div><div><span><p class=\"\"><span>NVR reported second-quarter net income of $236.5 million, or $83.96 per diluted share, for the quarter ended June 30, 2026, down from $333.7 million and $108.54 per diluted share a year earlier. Consolidated revenues for Q2 2026 were $2.33 billion and declined to $4.21 billion for the six months ended June 30, 2026. The company cited a reduced homebuilding gross profit margin and contract land deposit impairments as contributors to lower profitability.</span></p><p class=\"\"><strong class=\"root-Tkn6WL2y\"><span>Financial Highlights</span></strong></p><ul class=\"list-bmN0_SHH list--padded-bmN0_SHH\"><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Net income (three months ended June 30, 2026): $236.5 million; diluted EPS: $83.96.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Consolidated revenues (Q2 2026): $2.33 billion; consolidated revenues (six months ended June 30, 2026): $4.21 billion.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Homebuilding revenues (Q2 2026): $2.28 billion.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Income before taxes (Q2 2026): $318.6 million; income tax expense: $82.2 million.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Gross profit margin — homebuilding (Q2 2026): 19.2% (down from 21.5% in Q2 2025).</span></li></ul><p class=\"\"><strong class=\"root-Tkn6WL2y\"><span>Business Highlights</span></strong></p><ul class=\"list-bmN0_SHH list--padded-bmN0_SHH\"><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>New orders in Q2 2026 increased 9% year-over-year to 5,885 units; average sales price of new orders was $437,100 (down 5% YoY).</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Settlements decreased 8% year-over-year to 5,058 units in Q2 2026; average settlement price was $450,700 (down 3% YoY).</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Backlog as of June 30, 2026 rose 9% on a unit basis to 10,998 homes and increased 5% on a dollar basis to $4.99 billion versus June 30, 2025.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Mortgage closed loan production in Q2 2026 totaled $1.35 billion; mortgage banking income before tax was $25.4 million.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Company reported operational headwinds including higher lot costs, pricing pressure from affordability challenges and weaker consumer sentiment, and contract land deposit impairments of approximately $21.7 million impacting homebuilding margins.</span></li></ul><p class=\"\"><span>Original SEC Filing: </span><a class=\"link-zw5jRdec icon-zw5jRdec\" href=\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/906163/000090616326000086/nvr-20260723.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">NVR INC [ NVR ] - 8-K - Jul. 23, 2026</a></p><section class=\"variant-secondary-Gmpzg_mv disclaimer-PlF2Sa64\"><b class=\"heading-wrapper-Gmpzg_mv\"><span class=\"heading-Gmpzg_mv\">Disclaimer</span></b><div class=\"content-Gmpzg_mv link-with-underline-Gmpzg_mv\"><span>This is an AI-powered summary. It may contain inaccuracies. Consider verifying important information with the source. Please note this summary is solely based on documents filed with the SEC.</span></div></section></span></div></div>",
            "link": "https://www.tradingview.com/news/tradingview:c76f77a49f3d4:0-nvr-reports-q2-net-income-236-5m-eps-83-96-revenues-2-33b/",
            "pub_date": "2026-07-24 02:03:01",
            "source": "TradingView",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
